JPA - Java Persistance API (ORM tool)

Java - Our classes
Persistence - Storage of Objects
API - Library

The fields are ROWS and Objects are the COLUMNS.

The Java classes that are marked with @Entity can be used as Persistent Object in the Hibernate.

The default file name will be Hibernate_cfg file

The word Transient in Java is used before the Persistent process. Before saving the Session in Hibernate.

 06/05/2019
 
 -- Spring Web MVC Integration with Hibernate --
 
 1. Dependencies:
 
 	(a) Spring ORM (Spring Library, exclusively used to link with Hibernate tools)
 	(b) Hibernate
 
 2. Configuration class (Spring Web Configuration file)
 
	 (a) Data source
	 (b) Local Session Factory
	 (c) Hibernate Transaction Manager (will take part in managing the transactions).
	 
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Spring JPA - Java persistance API

1. Converting an existing Spring MVC application to Spring Boot
2. Dependency (jar) for stand alone application
3. Project facet changes
4. Wiring the Spring Boot Main configuration class 


JPA uses CGLIB - Code Generation Library

This will generated at the runtime.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Security:-

Endpoints:

Roles - {Admin, User}

/searchlocation/{countryName} - User

/updatelocation{locationId}/{cityName} - Admin

/Welcome - anonymous



Configuration step involved in the EventManagementSecurity class for Security.

1. We need to override the configure() methods
2. Setting Creating Roles and Usernames and Password using AuthenticationManagerBuilder 
3. Pattern based restriction for endpoints via MVC Matcher ../root/**
4. Mapping those endpoints to specific Roles
5. Deciding whether to choose inMemory auth. or Database Auth. or JWT Auth. (Web Tokens)
6. Password encryptions (with and without)
7. Disable CSRF (Cross Site Request Forgery)
8. Access Denied Exception handling

